    <body>
      <group id="content" extype="content">
        <trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>Validate a production flow and version</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>This procedure shows how to create a new production flow and a first version for lean manufacturing.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Validate a production flow and version</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This procedure shows how to create a new production flow and a first version for lean manufacturing.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Prerequisites: The production parameters for Lean manufacturing and the units of measure for class time must be defined.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You need to define a Value stream and a Production group.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Refer to the white papers on Lean manufacturing to familiarize yourself with the concepts of production flows and activities.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This procedure refers to the legal entity USMF in demo data.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>However, assuming that the legal entity is configured for Lean manufacturing, other legal entities can be used.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Create a production flow</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Go to Production control &gt; Setup &gt; Lean production flow &gt; Production flows.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click New.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Name field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Description field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="115" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Name field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the list, click the link in the selected row.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="117" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>A value stream is an operating unit that spans over all activities and flows of the value stream.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="118" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>At this stage, operating units are limited to a legal entity and have no further functionality.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="119" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Production group field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="120" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the list, click the link in the selected row.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="121" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Production groups allow the definition of material, labor, and WIP accounts for a production process.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="122" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To associate the accounting context to a production flow, a production group must be selected.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="123" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Save.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="124" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Create a production flow version</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="125" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Add.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="126" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Expiration date field, enter a date and time.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="127" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can update the Expiration date of the version at any given time, even for active versions.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="128" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use the expiration of the version to plan for a phase out of a version.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="129" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click OK.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="130" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the list, mark the selected row.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="131" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Unit field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="132" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Select the Takt unit.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="133" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Average takt time field, enter a number.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="134" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For the takt control of the production flow version, define a targeted average takt time.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="135" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The takt is defined as quantity  per time period.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="136" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the given example, the takt time is 0.2 hours per 10 pieces.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="137" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For a working time of 8 hours, this corresponds to a daily throughput capacity of 400 pieces.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="138" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Quantity per cycle field, enter a number.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="139" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Expand or collapse the Version details section.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="140" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Minimum takt time field, enter a number.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="141" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The minimum takt time must be less than or equal to the average takt time.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="142" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Maximum takt time field, enter a number.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="143" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The maximum takt time must be higher than or equal to the Average takt time.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="144" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Enter a number of days in the Period for actual cycle time</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="145" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The period for actual cycle time is the number of days that jobs are aggregated from the actual minute backwards to calculate the actual cycle time.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="146" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The value can be changed at any time and is only used for the calculation of the actual cycle times.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="147" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Save.</source>
        </trans-unit>
